generate_moves.prompt:
Your name is agent_1. You are in an environment with the following public information:
{environment->public_information}
You have the following private knowledge:
{agents->agent_1->private_information}
This is the cooperative global goal to achieve:
{agents->agent_1->goal}
Think step by step and produce an ordered list of primitive moves (one per line) that you will perform, using only disks A..H and following the Tower of Hanoi rules. Use the exact line format: 'agent_1: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'.

Your name is agent_2. You are in an environment with the following public information:
{environment->public_information}
You have the following private knowledge:
{agents->agent_2->private_information}
This is the cooperative global goal to achieve:
{agents->agent_2->goal}
Think step by step and produce an ordered list of primitive moves (one per line) that you will perform, using only disks I..O and following the Tower of Hanoi rules. Use the exact line format: 'agent_2: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'.

plan_pddl.prompt:
You are the orchestrator. You will receive two move lists produced by the agents. Integrate them to produce a final PDDL domain and problem that, when solved by FastDownwards, yields a plan consistent with both agents' moves and the Tower of Hanoi rules.
Here is the move list from agent_1:
{moves_agent_1}
Here is the move list from agent_2:
{moves_agent_2}
This is the public environment information:
{environment->public_information}
This is your coordination goal:
{agents->orchestrator->goal}
Think step by step: identify any conflicts, ensure each agent's permitted disks are enforced, keep actions distinct, and produce a complete PDDL domain and problem. Enclose the PDDL domain between <domain></domain> tags and the PDDL problem between <problem></problem> tags. Make sure the PDDL is suitable for FastDownwards.
